node.text:
Update on our @vanderpumpdogs China Rescue Center! Since being forced to relocate as the government in China will no longer allow animal facilities within city limits, we have been breaking ground and getting our new shelter prepared to be the new long-term home for our Yulin Survivors! So far we have installed our kennels, and are preparing the foundation to build all the rooms we need for grooming, medical, living rooms and a play area for all the dogs to play in! This has become a huge undertaking for our amazing team in China. We don’t know what we would do without them. In addition, we have needed to safely transport all of our China rescues by a temperature controlled vehicle to safely bring them to the new shelter soon. With the high temperatures in China, most would not have survived the long trip to the new shelter without a temperature controlled vehicle.

Our team was not prepared to move, when we were suddenly forced to move outside of the city limits. But we’ve adapted and have created an amazing new facility to call home and to care for the dogs we have in our care. We hope to make this shelter a new long-term home to our current and future Yulin Survivors. Click the link in my bio to find out more! Thank you! 🐾

node.text:
Diana has one of the most heartbreaking stories we’ve seen at the @VanderpumpDogs Rescue Center since our doors opened in 2016. Diana was tragically hit by car while she was pregnant and was left on the side of the road to die. Someone then dragged her into a tollbooth where her body went into shock from the accident, and she gave birth to four premature babies. We knew we had to rescue her immediately to give her a chance. 

We took her to @MASHvet where she was diagnosed with a severe bone infection from the trauma, a blood infection, anemia and ehrlichiosis. The bone infection was so bad we were left with no other choice than to have her left hind leg amputated. To make matters worse, her right hip was completely dislocated, and we couldn’t wait until it was healed to amputate given the severity of the infection. We were also forced to separate her from her babies (something we would never do under normal circumstances)as she was on several antibiotics and her milk would have been lethal for her babies to consume. As a result, we’ve had our wonderful medical fosters help bottle feed them since last month.

She has now been treated and just came out of her second surgery @MASHvet to correct her right hip and restore her mobility. Diana is still not able to walk on her own, and is fully reliant on our staff to help assist her with walking and going outside. However, she is currently going through rehab to regain her strength and build her muscles, and she is starting to come out of her shell and feel a bit better.

She has a long road ahead; but soon she will be a happy healthy dog again. Her puppies are also, against all odds, doing fine. She is also looking for her forever home! 

Please keep her in your thoughts and prayers! We greatly appreciate all of your support. Please visit www.vanderpumpdogs.org if you’d like to get involved. Thank you!

node.text: Each year at @vanderpumpdogs we reflect on the year before and create a time capsule of all the accomplishments our team achieves. Watching this video reminds me that Giggy’s legacy will live on. It was because of our little man that we started our rescue Foundation, and he has been responsible for so many dogs saved. What we are most proud of in 2020 is the fact we have found furever homes for 2,020 dogs domestically at our Rescue Center in Los Angeles, and 2021 will kick off with our 2021st adoption! This wouldn’t have been possible without the support of our loyal dog-loving community! At the end of the day, the care and well-being of all dogs worldwide will always be at the forefront of what we do at the Vanderpump Dog Foundation and, when we work together, whether it is through petitions, social awareness, volunteering or more, true everlasting change can and will be made. It is our hope that together we can make the greatest impact on these loving creatures’ lives! Here’s to a better tomorrow! Happy 2021! Xo Lisa #YearInReview #VanderpumpDogs

node.text:
I am so proud of our @VanderpumpDogs newest initiative, the #VanderpumpVeterans Program. Please watch EJay & Roxi’s video - it brought tears to my eyes. Dogs are such a huge part of my life, and seeing them find homes is always rewarding, but we have been so excited to start our Veterans Program to give back to the humans who give so much for us, too. 

We are now finding rescue dogs that are a good fit; rehabilitating them and putting them through an intensive training program, to become a service dog to a Veteran who suffers from post traumatic stress disorder. We are not only saving dogs, but are also trying to change and improve the lives of these brave men and women who have sacrificed their lives for our country.

In honor of Veterans Month I will be sharing some highlights. We’d also love to hear your stories if you’re a Veteran who loves and depends on their companion animal (service dog trained or not!) - post your story and tag #VanderpumpVeterans so we can see it and share. If you’d like to find out more about our program, or be a part of it, visit VanderpumpDogs.org (link in bio!) Thank you to all the brave Veterans who have served our country. Our Foundation looks forward to helping give back to you! 💙🇺🇸♥️ #Veterans #Grateful

Thank you all for coming to our @VanderpumpDogs 5th annual World Dog Day … it was a HUGE success!! 💗 From the amazing support of the City of West Hollywood (who co-sponsored our event), to our community, to adorable dogs, friends, food, music, sponsors and vendors - we all had such a great day ! A special thank you to @wehocity and our amazing sponsors, @zappos @hillspet @surrules @tomtom @pumprestaurant @mashvet @theabbeyweho & @greendogdental ! We couldn’t have done this with you! 

We couldn’t be more grateful to everyone that came out to support our Vanderpump Dogs 501(c)(3) non-profit Foundation and help us continue our life saving rescue mission for doggies all over the world! 

‘Til next year...! 🎉💗🐶 (thank you to @palmandocean and @nikkiryanphotography for the amazing photos!)

I so hope to see you all there and spend the day celebrating dogs the way they deserve to be celebrated!
